<subSubSection id="B7BF6529FFDCFF91FF30FD7C8DFEFBBE" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="FF1A36A2FFDCFF91FF30FD7C8E62FD37" blockId="3.[189,310,716,740]" box="[189,310,716,742]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis id="CDD1EAB0FFDCFF91FF30FD7C8E62FD37" bold="true" box="[189,310,716,742]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FF1A36A2FFDCFF91FF30FD4B8EBCFC36" blockId="3.[189,1399,762,1000]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<taxonomicName id="38A54D21FFDCFF91FF30FD4B8E4BFCC5" box="[189,287,763,788]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CDD1EAB0FFDCFF91FF30FD4B8E4BFCC5" box="[189,287,763,788]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Begonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sect. 
<emphasis id="CDD1EAB0FFDCFF91FEE7FD4A8D42FCC5" box="[362,534,762,788]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Microtuberosa</emphasis>
sect. nov. is most closely related to 
<emphasis id="CDD1EAB0FFDCFF91FC53FD4B8CA3FCC5" box="[990,1015,763,788]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">B.</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName id="38A54D21FFDCFF91FBCEFD4A8BAFFCC5" authority="A.DC., 1861 (Müll.Berol.)" authorityName="A.DC., 1861 (Müll.Berol.)" box="[1091,1275,762,788]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Trachelocarpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CDD1EAB0FFDCFF91FBCEFD4A8BAFFCC5" box="[1091,1275,762,788]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Trachelocarpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and three species of 
<emphasis id="CDD1EAB0FFDCFF91FEB1FCAE8E01FCE6" box="[316,341,798,823]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">B.</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName id="38A54D21FFDCFF91FE11FCAD8D51FCE6" authority="A.DC., 1859 (Klotzsch)" authorityName="A.DC., 1859 (Klotzsch)" box="[412,517,797,823]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Gaerdtia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CDD1EAB0FFDCFF91FE11FCAD8D51FCE6" box="[412,517,797,823]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Gaerdtia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both of these sections are endemic to eastern Brazil and differ markedly from sect. 
<emphasis id="CDD1EAB0FFDCFF91FEB4FCF18EB1FC8A" box="[313,485,833,859]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Microtuberosa</emphasis>
sect. nov. in both their habit and Foral characteristics (see 
<tableCitation id="B2270319FFDCFF91FB1BFCF18BB8FC8A" box="[1174,1260,833,859]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="4.[189,258,268,294]" captionTargetBox="[189,1397,382,1199]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Table 1. Comparison between Begonia sect. Microtuberosa Moonlight &amp; Tebbitt sect. nov. and closely related sections." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/ABDA662AFFDBFF96FF30FEBC8E2EFE99" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" tableUuid="ABDA662AFFDBFF96FF30FEBC8E2EFE99">Table 1</tableCitation>
). However, all three sections share their Flaments fused at least at the base and 
<emphasis id="CDD1EAB0FFDCFF91FC7DFCD58B5DFCAF" box="[1008,1033,869,894]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">B.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="CDD1EAB0FFDCFF91FBDCFCD48BA9FCAF" box="[1105,1277,868,894]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Microtuberosa</emphasis>
sect. nov. further shares its androecium morphology with 
<emphasis id="CDD1EAB0FFDCFF91FD7EFC388C58FC70" box="[755,780,904,929]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">B.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="CDD1EAB0FFDCFF91FCDFFC388CFFFC70" box="[850,939,904,929]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Pereira</emphasis>
and its lack of bracteoles with 
<emphasis id="CDD1EAB0FFDCFF91FAADFC388A6DFC70" box="[1312,1337,904,929]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">B.</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName id="38A54D21FFDCFF91FF30FC1A8E21FC15" authority="A.DC., 1861 (Müll.Berol.)" authorityName="A.DC., 1861 (Müll.Berol.)" box="[189,373,938,964]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Trachelocarpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CDD1EAB0FFDCFF91FF30FC1A8E21FC15" box="[189,373,938,964]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Trachelocarpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The majority of both Foral and vegetative characters are, however, markedly different among the three sections.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FF1A36A2FFDCFF91FF30FBA08DFEFBBE" blockId="3.[189,1399,1039,1136]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<taxonomicName id="38A54D21FFDCFF91FF30FBA08E4BFBF8" box="[189,287,1040,1065]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CDD1EAB0FFDCFF91FF30FBA08E4BFBF8" box="[189,287,1040,1065]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Begonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sect. 
<emphasis id="CDD1EAB0FFDCFF91FEE9FBBF8D44FBF8" box="[356,528,1039,1065]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Microtuberosa</emphasis>
sect. nov. is readily identiFed as the only Neotropical section of 
<taxonomicName id="38A54D21FFDCFF91FA98FBA08A23FBF8" box="[1301,1399,1040,1065]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CDD1EAB0FFDCFF91FA98FBA08A23FBF8" box="[1301,1399,1040,1065]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Begonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with male Fowers with four or fewer stamens, and the combination of ovaries with two or three locules and entire placentas, and a tuberous habit.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B7BF6529FFDCFF91FF30FB278BAAFB0E" box="[189,1278,1175,1248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="FF1A36A2FFDCFF91FF30FB278E10FB60" blockId="3.[189,1278,1175,1248]" box="[189,324,1175,1201]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<heading id="A45281CEFFDCFF91FF30FB278E10FB60" bold="true" box="[189,324,1175,1201]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" reason="6">
<emphasis id="CDD1EAB0FFDCFF91FF30FB278E10FB60" bold="true" box="[189,324,1175,1201]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FF1A36A2FFDCFF91FF30FB758BAAFB0E" blockId="3.[189,1278,1175,1248]" box="[189,1278,1221,1248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
The name ‘ 
<emphasis id="CDD1EAB0FFDCFF91FECEFB758EBBFB0E" box="[323,495,1221,1247]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Microtuberosa</emphasis>
’ emphasises the diminutive and tuberous habit of the type species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B7BF6529FFDCFF91FF30FAB78E0CFAF0" box="[189,344,1287,1313]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="FF1A36A2FFDCFF91FF30FAB78E0CFAF0" blockId="3.[189,344,1287,1312]" box="[189,344,1287,1313]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis id="CDD1EAB0FFDCFF91FF30FAB78E0CFAF0" bold="true" box="[189,344,1287,1313]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Type species</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B7BF6529FFDCFF91FF30FA868DB9FA81" box="[189,749,1333,1360]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="FF1A36A2FFDCFF91FF30FA868DB9FA81" blockId="3.[189,749,1333,1360]" box="[189,749,1333,1360]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<taxonomicName id="38A54D21FFDCFF91FF30FA868DDFFA9E" authority="Moonlight &amp; Tebbitt" authorityName="Moonlight &amp; Tebbitt" box="[189,651,1333,1359]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elachista" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="CDD1EAB0FFDCFF91FF30FA868EC4FA9E" box="[189,400,1333,1359]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Begonia elachista</emphasis>
Moonlight &amp; Tebbitt
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D6E257CBFFDCFF91FD1FFA868DB9FA81" box="[658,749,1334,1360]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B7BF6529FFDCFF91FF30FAC78C5BF967" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="description">
<paragraph id="FF1A36A2FFDCFF91FF30FAC78E1AFA40" blockId="3.[189,1399,1399,1718]" box="[189,334,1399,1425]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<heading id="A45281CEFFDCFF91FF30FAC78E1AFA40" bold="true" box="[189,334,1399,1425]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" reason="6">
<emphasis id="CDD1EAB0FFDCFF91FF30FAC78E1AFA40" bold="true" box="[189,334,1399,1425]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FF1A36A2FFDCFF91FF30FA158C5BF967" blockId="3.[189,1399,1399,1718]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Caulescent, tuberous herbs, perennial. Stems erect. Stipules persistent, entire. Leaves alternate, 2–4(–6), basiFxed, blade symmetrical or subsymmetrical, veins palmate. InForescence axillary, an asymmetric dichasial cyme, protandrous, bracts persistent. Male Fowers: with 2–4 free perianth segments; stamens 2 or 4, Flaments united into a column for more than half their length, anthers elliptic, dehiscing via lateral slits, connective not projecting. Female Fowers: bracteoles absent, with 2–3 free perianth segments; ovary and fruit with 2–3 wings, wings equal, 2–3-locular, placentas entire, bearing ovules on both surfaces; styles 2–3, free to base, biFd from about ⅔ their height, stigmatic papillae in a once spirally twisted band. Fruit a capsule. Seeds not examined.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B7BF6529FFDCFF91FF30F96D8E7AF898" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="FF1A36A2FFDCFF91FF30F96D8E02F926" blockId="3.[189,342,1757,1783]" box="[189,342,1757,1783]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<heading id="A45281CEFFDCFF91FF30F96D8E02F926" bold="true" box="[189,342,1757,1783]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" reason="2">
<emphasis id="CDD1EAB0FFDCFF91FF30F96D8E02F926" bold="true" box="[189,342,1757,1783]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FF1A36A2FFDCFF91FF30F8BC8E7AF898" blockId="3.[189,1398,1804,1865]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">On a limestone outcrop in lowland Amazonian Peru to the east of the Chemillén Cordillera at an altitude of 430 m.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
